# 🚂 WaitSure — IRCTC Waitlist Confirmation Predictor

> Predict whether your IRCTC waitlisted train ticket will get confirmed — powered by a full ML pipeline with explainability and a Streamlit UI.

---

## Overview

WaitSure is an end-to-end machine learning project that predicts the confirmation probability of waitlisted Indian Railway (IRCTC) tickets. It combines three real-world datasets, trains and benchmarks seven ML models, and exposes predictions through both a CLI app and an interactive Streamlit web interface.

---

## Project Structure

```
ml-project/
├── project.py              # Full ML pipeline: data loading, training, evaluation, visualisation
├── predict_app.py          # CLI prediction app (dropdown-based interactive interface)
├── streamlit_app.py        # Streamlit web UI (wraps predict_app.py backend)
│
├── data/
│   ├── waitsure_200_merged.csv           # Core labelled dataset (~200 high-quality records)
│   ├── Railway Ticket Confirmation.csv   # 30,000 IRCTC PNR records
│   └── waiting list.csv                  # Waitlist status timeline features
│
├── models/
│   ├── waitsure_best_model.pkl           # Trained Random Forest model
│   ├── scaler.pkl                        # RobustScaler for numerical features
│   ├── encoders.pkl                      # Label encoders for categorical columns
│   └── feat_names.json                   # Ordered list of feature names
│
└── outputs/
    ├── classification_report.txt         # Precision / recall / F1 per class
    ├── model_report.csv                  # Benchmark table across all models
    ├── confusion_matrix.png
    ├── roc_curves.png
    ├── pr_curves.png
    ├── feature_importance.png / .csv
    ├── model_comparison.png
    ├── domain_insights.png
    ├── unsupervised_analysis.png
    └── decision_tree_rules.txt
```

---

## Algorithms Used

| Category | Algorithms |
|---|---|
| **Supervised** | Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, Random Forest, XGBoost, LightGBM, Voting Ensemble, Stacking Ensemble |
| **Unsupervised** | K-Means Clustering, PCA |
| **Resampling** | SMOTE (handles class imbalance) |
| **Explainability** | SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) |
| **Evaluation** | Accuracy, F1, AUC-ROC, MAE, RMSE, R², Cross-validated AUC |

---

## Model Performance

The best model is **Random Forest**, selected after benchmarking all seven algorithms:

| Model | Accuracy | F1 Score | AUC-ROC | CV AUC |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Random Forest ★** | 99.78% | 0.9978 | 1.000 | 1.000 |
| LightGBM | 99.80% | 0.9980 | 1.000 | 1.000 |
| Stacking Ensemble | 99.76% | 0.9976 | 1.000 | 1.000 |
| Voting Ensemble | 99.78% | 0.9978 | 1.000 | 1.000 |
| XGBoost | 99.70% | 0.9970 | 0.9998 | 0.9993 |
| Decision Tree | 99.75% | 0.9975 | 0.9992 | 0.9995 |
| Logistic Regression | 98.31% | 0.9833 | 0.9991 | 0.9982 |

---

## Features Used

The model is trained on 17 features:

- **Ticket info:** `train_no`, `train_type`, `travel_class`, `quota`, `source_station`, `destination`
- **Timing:** `days_before_travel`, `season`, `booking_urgency`
- **Waitlist signals:** `waitlist_number`, `total_seats`, `wl_seat_ratio`
- **Historical/derived:** `historical_confirm_rate`, `cancellation_trend`, `confirm_signal`, `cancel_pressure`, `is_premium_class`

---

## Installation

**Requirements:** Python 3.9+

```bash
pip install numpy pandas scikit-learn xgboost lightgbm imbalanced-learn shap joblib matplotlib seaborn streamlit
```

---

## Usage

### Run the Full ML Pipeline (train + evaluate + visualise)

```bash
python project.py
```

This will load and merge all three datasets, train all seven models, evaluate them, generate all output plots and reports, and save the best model to the `models/` folder.

### CLI Prediction App (interactive dropdowns)

```bash
python predict_app.py
```

Loads the pre-trained model and prompts you to select Train Number, Date, Class, Quota, etc. via dropdown menus, then prints the WaitSure prediction.

### Streamlit Web UI

```bash
streamlit run streamlit_app.py
```

Opens a browser-based IRCTC-styled UI. Select ticket parameters and get an instant confirmation probability with a visual result banner.

### Programmatic Prediction

```python
from predict_app import predict_ticket

predict_ticket(
    train_no=12301,
    waitlist_number=14,
    travel_class="3A",
    quota="GN",
    source_station="NDLS",
    destination="HWH",
    days_before_travel=10,
    season="Non-Peak"
)
```

---

## Data Sources

| File | Description | Size |
|---|---|---|
| `waitsure_200_merged.csv` | Core hand-labelled dataset with rich features | ~200 records |
| `Railway Ticket Confirmation.csv` | IRCTC PNR records with confirmation status | ~30,000 records |
| `waiting list.csv` | Waitlist status timeline for feature engineering | — |

> **Note:** Update `DATA_PATHS` in `project.py` if your data files are in a different location.

---

## Outputs

After running `project.py`, the `outputs/` folder will contain:

- `classification_report.txt` — per-class precision, recall, F1
- `model_report.csv` — full benchmark table
- `confusion_matrix.png` — prediction error breakdown
- `roc_curves.png` / `pr_curves.png` — model discrimination curves
- `feature_importance.png` / `.csv` — top predictive features
- `model_comparison.png` — side-by-side model benchmark chart
- `domain_insights.png` — domain-specific EDA visualisations
- `unsupervised_analysis.png` — K-Means clustering + PCA plots
- `decision_tree_rules.txt` — human-readable decision tree logic

---

## Configuration

Edit the top of `project.py` to configure:

```python
SEED       = 42           # Random seed for reproducibility
OUTPUT_DIR = "outputs"    # Where plots and reports are saved
MODEL_DIR  = "models"     # Where trained models are saved

DATA_PATHS = {
    "main":         "data/waitsure_200_merged.csv",
    "confirmation": "data/Railway Ticket Confirmation.csv",
    "waitlist":     "data/waiting list.csv",
}
```

